    • Field Detail

      • DEBUG

        public static final boolean DEBUG
        Enables debug mode. Debug mode will output verbose logging. Recognized values are "enabled", "disabled". The default value is "disabled".
        See Also:
        ConfigDefaults

      • DRIVER

        public static final String DRIVER
        The WebDriver used for the test run. Possible values are: Chrome, Firefox, InternetExplorer, and PhantomJS (the default). This value may be overridden by using annotations.
        See Also:
        Chrome, Firefox, InternetExplorer, PhantomJS

      • ENDPOINT

        public static final String ENDPOINT
        The endpoint used for the test run. By default this is a null value, and will cause a failed System.exit() call to occur if null. This value is used to resolve desired URLs when requesting page objects from page factories.
        See Also:
        AbstractSuite

      • LOGGING_PREFIX

        public static final String LOGGING_PREFIX
        The prefix used when logging. By default this is set to "TestNG-Selenium".

      • SCREENSIZE

        public static final String SCREENSIZE
        The default screen size used for test runs. Possible values are: LargeDesktop, Desktop, Tablet, and Phone. The default screen size is Phone.
        See Also:
        LargeDesktop, Desktop, Tablet, Phone

      • TMPDIR

        public static final String TMPDIR
        The temporary directory used to store screen shots, cookie files, and other related data needed for test runs. The default value is set to the platform specific default temp directory location.

      • USER_AGENT

        public static final String USER_AGENT
        The default User-Agent string to use in the WebDriver. This overrides the WebDriver's default User-Agent. This value may be overridden on a test by test basis via annotations.
        See Also:
        UserAgent
